details.address: 300 Technology Center Way Suite 200, Rock Hill, SC 29730
details.description: A coffee cafe merging robotic innovation with a premium espresso experience in a modern and inviting atmosphere. Our robotic barista does all the work while you get to enjoy. The elegant industrial vibe offers an elevated style and experience from the moment you enter the doors. Multiple seating areas, an open layout, 20-foot concrete columns and windows as far as the eye can see that provide a stunning backdrop. We also offer pastries made by local bakers.

reviews_data.review_text: What a fun space! Lots of seating options, even private spaces for a quiet cup of coffee. Coffee is great and the gluten free/dairy free muffin from Wild Flour Bakery was delicious. Owners are super friendly and make you feel right at home.

Atmosphere was spot on for me, was just put off by the coffee. It wasn’t bad; minimal bitterness, good overall taste, but just not strong enough. Limited options for customization was a huge influence  as well.
This is a must-visit spot in Rock Hill. If you are looking for a quality cup of coffee along with a cozy atmosphere you have to check this out.

Such an amazing spot! The atmosphere is warm and welcoming, and the coffee is fantastic. It’s the perfect place to get work done, relax with friends, or even host a meeting in their spacious conference area. I also think the robotic coffee machines are super cool and neat!

Chai latte was delicious! Seeing your coffee made by a machine is really cool lol. We so luckily got to meet the owner, she was so welcoming & down to earth. Definitely give this place a try! The prices are reasonable & the space is beautiful.
Amazing coffee, gorgeous and relaxing space.
